{{Use Indian English|date=October 2018}}
'''Dihanaam''' is a type of congregational prayer sung by women in [[Assam]] in praise of the Assamese saint [[Srimanta Sankardev|Sankardev]]. Instruments like the ''[[Naqareh|Negera]]'', ''[[Taal (instrument)|taal]]'', ''[[khol]]'' and also [[Clapping|hand-clapping]] is used in it. The songs are derived from Vaishnava religious scriptures like ''[[Kirtan Ghoxa|Kirtan-ghosa]]''. The songs are sung in call and response style.

