{{Tibetan Buddhism}}

The '''Gsung-'bum''' ([[Standard Tibetan|Tibetan]]: "collected works") are the collected [[Buddhism|Buddhist]] writings of a [[lama]],<ref>[http://www.cihts.ac.in/lang/en/library/tibetan.aspx Shantarakshita Library] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100309032007/http://www.cihts.ac.in/lang/en/library/tibetan.aspx |date=2010-03-09 }}</ref> specifically one from [[Mongolia]] or [[Tibet]],<ref>[http://wordpress.tsadra.org/?p=960 Tibetan Genre Classifications] from the [[Tsadra Foundation]]</ref> as distinguished from the [[Bka'-'gyur]] and [[Bstan-'gyur]].

