{{Jainism}}
'''Jambuswami''' was the last [[kevali]] (omniscient being) of the present half cycle of time as per the Jain scriptures. He was the third and last ''anubuddha kevali'' after [[Mahavira]].<ref>{{citation|last1=Kshamasagar|first1=Muni|author-link=Kshamasagar|title=''jain darshan''|year=2009|publisher= Maitreesamoh|p=132|isbn=81-7628-017-8}}</ref> After teaching for 39 years, Jambuswami attained ''[[Moksha (Jainism)|nirvāna]]'' (liberation) at Mathura Chaurasi.<ref>{{citation|last1=Pramansagar|first1=Muni|author-link=Pramansagar|title=''jain dharma aur darshan''|year=2014|publisher= Nirgranth Foundation|p=46|isbn=81-7483-007-3}}</ref>

