'''Marc Camille Chaimowicz''' is a London-based contemporary artist whose works are in the [[Museum of Modern Art]], [[Tate Modern]], and [[Victoria and Albert Museum]] collections.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.moma.org/artists/34803?locale=en |title=Marc Camille Chaimowicz |publisher=MoMA.org |accessdate=February 15, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.tate.org.uk/art/artists/marc-camille-chaimowicz-882|title=Marc Camille Chaimowicz born 1947 {{!}} Tate|last=Tate|work=Tate|access-date=2018-03-14|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://m.vam.ac.uk/collections/search/?offset=0&limit=10&q=Marc+Camille+Chaimowicz&commit=Search&quality=0|title=V&A Search|website=m.vam.ac.uk|language=en|access-date=2018-03-14}}</ref> His cross-disciplinary work in painting, drawing, collage, sculpture, installation, furniture, lighting, ceramics, textiles, and wallpaper challenges the categorical divisions between art and design.
Chaimowicz was born in 1947<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mitpress.mit.edu/books/marc-camille-chaimowicz|title=Marc Camille Chaimowicz: Celebration? Realife|website=mitpress.mit.edu|language=en|access-date=2018-04-14}}</ref> in postwar Paris to a Polish Jewish father and French Catholic mother. The family moved to England when the artist was eight years old and settled in London, where he still lives and works. His first solo museum exhibition in the United States is on view now at the [[Jewish Museum (Manhattan)|Jewish Museum]] in New York.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thejewishmuseum.org/exhibitions/marc-camille-chaimowicz-your-place-or-mine|title=Marc Camille Chaimowicz: Your Place or Mine…|website=The Jewish Museum|access-date=2018-03-14}}</ref>
